As the world marks the 2018 World Oral Health Day, Dr Seye Logede, a Principal Dental Officer, says the general attitude of Nigerians to oral health has significantly improved unlike in times past. Logede, who works at the Oral Diagnosis Unit, National Hospital, ‎Abuja, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Tuesday in Abuja that the use of social media contributed to the success recorded. Logede, who is also Vice-Chairman, Dental Association of Nigeria, Abuja Chapter, noted that poor oral health could affect a person’s general health and well-being as the mouth is the gateway to the body. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from The NEWS. Click here to read the full text on the original website.